description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the above posts in a busy payroll department responsible for the payment of 103,000 NHS employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have a minimum of six years experience within an NHS payroll department, experience at manager level and possess an expert knowledge in payroll regulations, legislation and NHS conditions of service. Applicants must also have an expert knowledge of ESR and be able to demonstrate well developed customer service skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should also have the ability to work to strict deadlines in a pressurised environment, and should demonstrate a positive attitude and a sympathetic and patient personality, together with good organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership in order to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Michelle Pye&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Michelle.Pye@Northumbria.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0191 6073494&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 12th November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
